<p>Under tort law a person who is <strong>NOT AN AGGRESSOR</strong> may act reasonably if <strong>NECESSARY</strong> to protect their <strong>own safety</strong>.    </p>
<p>Modernly the person can &quot;hold her ground&quot; and has is <strong>no duty to retreat</strong> in most jurisdictions.    </p>
<p><strong>Aggressors</strong> are people who have unreasonably created or increased <strong>dangers to others</strong>.</p>
